  "title": "Securing Serverless Handlers Using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide explains how to secure serverless functions built with FastAPI in Python 3.12+, focusing on authentication, authorization, and best practices for securing APIs.",
  "key_points": [
    "Use `FastAPI` for building secure and fast APIs.",
    "Implement `OAuth2` for user authentication and token-based access control.",
    "Utilize `Depends` decorator to pass dependencies (like OAuth2 security scopes) into routes.",
    "Apply `security` object in FastAPI for defining security schemes like API Key, Basic Auth, and JWT.",
